{"bookResponse":{"bookId":"2ad4ecbb8e24f6cd9efcac897a233cf2","locale":"en_US","title":"macOS User Guide","meta":{"productVersion":"13.0","platformOSVersion":"13.0","icon":"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png","build_date":"Wed Mar 22 20:19:57 GMT 2023","product":"mac-help","creationDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","framework":"duck-15.4.0:goose-2.15.4:cuckoo-4.2.0"},"tocId":"MH43558","bookInfo":{"versionsDetails":[{"productVersion":"14.0","displayVersion":"macOS Sonoma 14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"14.0"},{"productVersion":"13.0","displayVersion":"macOS Ventura 13","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"13.0"},{"productVersion":"12.0","displayVersion":"macOS Monterey 12","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"12.0"},{"productVersion":"11.0","displayVersion":"macOS Big Sur 11.0","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"11.0"},{"productVersion":"10.15","displayVersion":"macOS Catalina 10.15","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.15"},{"productVersion":"10.14","displayVersion":"macOS Mojave 10.14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.14"},{"productVersion":"10.13","displayVersion":"macOS High Sierra","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.13"}]},"articles":[{"articleId":{"id":"BK_2AD4ECBB8E24F6CD9EFCAC897A233CF2_MCHL1D734309","locale":"en_US"},"meta":{"createDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","publishedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","archive":"false","ownerName":"apd migration","modifiedBy":"apd migration","version":"1","unPublished":false,"contentModel":"book"},"content":{"main":{"title":"Use Continuity to work across Apple devices","summary":"When your Mac and other supported devices recognize they’re near each other, features are enabled that let them work together."},"sections":[{"level":"1","text":"<body dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mchl1d734309\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic dark-mode-enabled\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mchl1d734309\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Finder.png\"></figure><h1>Use Continuity to work across Apple devices</h1><p>With Continuity, you can use your Mac together with your other Apple devices to work smarter and move seamlessly between your devices.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/1eca77c13e90f8c687c6b11a93c30f65.png\" alt=\"An iPhone showing a FaceTime call, next to a Mac where the call is being handed off, indicated by the Handoff icon on the FaceTime app icon near the right end of the Dock.\" height=\"278\" width=\"466\" originalImageName=\"Art/S2074_LifestyleFTHandoff.png\"></figure><p>To use Continuity features, <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=sign-in-with-your-apple-id&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOS0159E54B&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">sign in with the same Apple ID</a> on all your devices. In addition, your devices must have Wi-Fi and Bluetooth turned on, and meet system requirements. See the Apple Support article <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/HT204689\" class=\"URL\">System requirements for Continuity on Mac, iPhone, iPad, and Apple Watch</a>.</p><div id=\"apd97374ebae8f64\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">AirDrop</h2><p>AirDrop lets you quickly share photos, videos, contacts, and anything else, with anyone near you—wirelessly. It makes sharing to iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, and Mac as simple as dragging and dropping. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=airdrop-mac-send-files-devices&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH35868&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use AirDrop on your Mac to send files to devices near you</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchlf9850227\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">AirPlay to Mac</h2><p>Share, play, or present content from another Apple device to the screen of your Mac. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-your-mac-to-be-an-airplay-receiver&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLEEE00EC8&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up your Mac to be an AirPlay Receiver</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchlf20a3bce\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Auto Unlock and Approve with Apple Watch</h2><p>Use your Apple Watch to unlock your Mac or approve authentication requests from your Mac, without having to enter a password. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=unlock-your-mac-with-apple-watch&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL4F800A42&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Unlock your Mac and approve requests with Apple Watch</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchlb4b27deb\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Continuity Camera</h2><p><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=use-iphone-as-a-webcam&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL77879B8A&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use your iPhone as a webcam on Mac</a>, or <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=insert-photos-documents-iphone-ipad&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL9AEBDC99&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">take a picture or scan a document</a> with your nearby iPhone or iPad and have it appear instantly on your Mac. See the Apple Support article <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/HT213244\" class=\"URL\">Continuity Camera: Use iPhone as a webcam for Mac</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchlf2f30404\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Continuity Markup</h2><p>Edit a PDF document or image on your Mac and display it on your nearby iPhone or iPad, where you can write and sketch on it using Markup tools—and Apple Pencil on iPad—and instantly view the changes on your Mac. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=mark-up-files&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL1FD88863&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Mark up files</a>. </p></div><div id=\"mchlf3a699c3\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Continuity Sketch</h2><p>Draw a sketch using your nearby iPhone or iPad and have the sketch appear instantly on your Mac. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=insert-sketches-from-iphone-or-ipad&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL74E7C6DF&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Insert sketches with Continuity Sketch</a>. </p></div><div id=\"apd02da200a0e0d4\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Handoff</h2><p>Start a document, an email, or a message on one device and pick up where you left off on another device. Handoff works with apps like Mail, Safari, Maps, Messages, Reminders, Calendar, Contacts, Pages, Numbers, and Keynote. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=hand-off-between-devices&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL732D3C0A&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Pick up where you left off with Handoff</a>. </p></div><div id=\"apdbfe514474aaf4\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Instant Hotspot</h2><p>No Wi‑Fi? No problem. Your Mac can connect to the internet using the personal hotspot on your iPhone or iPad when they’re within range of each other—no setup is required. Your iPhone or iPad automatically appears in the Wi‑Fi menu on your Mac—just select it to turn on your hotspot. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=iphone-ipad-connect-mac-internet&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL7594E36F&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use an iPhone or iPad to connect your Mac to the internet</a>.</p></div><div id=\"apdbfd706d564444\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Phone Calls</h2><p>When you want to make or answer a phone call, don’t reach for your iPhone—use your Mac. You can start calls from FaceTime, Contacts, Safari, Mail, Maps, Spotlight, and many other apps. When someone calls you, a notification appears. Just click the notification to answer. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=facetime&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL390E9463&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Make and receive phone calls in FaceTime</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchle4d00286\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Sidecar</h2><p>When you use your iPad as a second display, you can have your iPad show the same apps and windows as your Mac, or extend your workspace by showing different apps and windows. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=use-your-ipad-as-a-second-display&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLF3C6F7AE&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use your iPad as a second display for your Mac</a>. </p></div><div id=\"apdbd4b140129384\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">SMS Messages</h2><p>Send and receive SMS and MMS text messages right from your Mac. When friends send you text messages, regardless of what phone they have, you can respond from whichever device is closest. All the messages that appear on your iPhone appear on your Mac, too. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=messages&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=ICHT8A28BB9A&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Set up iPhone to get SMS texts</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchl62bf212c\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Universal Clipboard</h2><p>Copy text, images, photos, and videos on one Apple device and then paste the content on another Apple device. For example, you can copy a recipe from Safari on your Mac, then paste it into Notes on your nearby iPhone. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=copy-and-paste-between-devices&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL70368996&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Copy and paste between devices from your Mac</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchl9da1fda9\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Universal Control</h2><p>When your Mac is near another Mac or iPad, you can use a single keyboard and trackpad, or a connected mouse, to work across the devices. You can even drag content between them—for example, you can sketch a drawing with Apple Pencil on iPad, then drag it to your Mac to drop into a Keynote presentation. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=keyboard-mouse-control-mac-ipad&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL412FAECF&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use one keyboard and mouse to control Mac and iPad</a>.</p></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-icloud-on-your-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36834&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up iCloud features on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/HT204681\" class=\"URL\">Apple Support article: Use Continuity to connect your Mac, iPhone, iPad, and Apple Watch</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","DisplayVersion/macOS Ventura 13","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ContentMode/liveContent","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON","ArchivalStatus/Archived","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"120736"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"135880"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"135315"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","displayName":"mac","articleCount":"85819"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName":"platform","displayName":"platform","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"Archived","name":"Archived","englishName":"Archived","displayName":"Archived","articleCount":"124678"},{"key":"ArchivalStatus","name":"ArchivalStatus","englishName":"ArchivalStatus","displayName":"ArchivalStatus","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndexOFF","name":"ExternalIndexOFF","englishName":"ExternalIndexOFF","displayName":"ExternalInde